Greetings from Shree Vallabh Gaushala. Gaushala is a well-known pilgrimage place where we worship cows. Worshipping cows, feeding them, and being with them brings tons of positive energy. We are determined to make our cows happy and loved by providing the highest protection, care and natural living. God Shree Krishan wishes \"Let the cows be in front of me, on my either side, behind me. I will always be in the middle of cows.” in the dasama skanda (10th Canto) of Srimad Bhagavatham.

  • Due to the inspiration of Shree Kishore Chandraji Maharaj, “Gopalan Kendra” (Village cattle camp) was established in many villages for the protection of cows.

  • Raising Nandi (bull calf) and giving it to various cowsheds for free.

  • Giving information on the manufacture of Panchgavya(five cow-derivatives) based medicines.

  • Preservation of pasture land and its development.

  • Organic farming promotion.

  • Shreevallabh Goshala is established to fulfil our primary duty to make our Gau-mata-Govansh reside peacefully and harmoniously in the entire nation and to remove the stigma of cow slaughtering.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"piw6cxszv","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

When there was a severe drought took place in year of 1987, the situation of our motherly figure Gomatawas very pity. In this hard timewith the help of inspiration of doctrines of Shree Mahaprabhuji and devotion to Lord Shree Krishna,ourNityaLeela. Shree Kishorechandraji Maharajshree established the importance of Gomata among the society.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"9p6mowgcc","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

The Mughal emperor Akbar had bestowed the title of “Goswami” on Prabhucharan Shree GusaijiVitthalnathji and the embodiment of the same is NityaLeela.Shree Kishorechandraji Maharajshree.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"zwgoz7of7","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

In perception of “કૃષ્ણસેવા સદા કાર્યા”preached by Mahaprabhuji Shree Vallabhacharyaji, It is firmly mentioned that if someone who really wants the gratification of Lord Shree Krishna, Goseva and devotion towards Lord Shree Krishna is only the way to this and in this term gratification of Gomata is the gratification of guardian of Gomata.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"x5ab7x2hu","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

The spirit of Goseva was always widely manifested all the time in conduct of Shree Kishorechandraji Maharajshree & because of the same he had been keeping himself persistently busy for Goseva and this way he dedicated his entire life towards Gomata.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"fmw3x1dpq","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

Therefore, not a single person whether he is from Gujarat or India, or all over the world & who also is a Gomata conserver was unaware of the name of Shree Kishorechandraji Maharajshree.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"kgqzsdj2d","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

NityaLeela. Shree Kishorechandraji Maharajshree used to preach explicitly that, “service, conservation, and protection are only the remedies of difficult situation occurred at present times in our country and world and this is only the way which will build conscientiousness in us & lead to the way of upliftment destroying the biliousness of us.”

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"x8zzutlb1","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"1mqi338by","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"20px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"26px","minWidth":"10px","fontWeight":"700","letterSpacing":"-0.2px","color":"#000","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"8px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"Establisher, Shree Vallabh Goshala","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"zhtvt2ulj","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

The way an immense compassion and affection KishorechandrajiMaharajshree had for Gomata along with better most sentiment & these same virtues of Shree Piyushbavashree assuredly draws attention of everyone and impacts anyone who gets in touch with him.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"w4oe1i58z","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

Shree Piyushbavashree’sinherent attraction towards Gomata explicitly reflects in nature of him and they consistently contemplates for progressive development of Shree VallabhGoshala established by Shree KishorechandrajiMaharajshree. For happily and prolonged dwelling of Gomata-Govansh, the decayed departments of Goshala are resurrected in year 2021 with the help of Sanskrit language in very protective manner along with the help of modern technology. Shree Piyushbavashree accomplished this resurrection task of Goshala departments by providing consistent hard work and guidance of him.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"edb1g7in2","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"left","fontWeight":"500","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

It has always been a straight forward approach of Goswami Shree Piyushbavashee that “As an ancestor and acharya of Shree Vallabhacharyaji, It is our prime duty to inspire entire VaishnavSrushti by applying principles of Shree Vallabh into routine conduct” & this approach clearly reflects in nature of Shree Piyushbavashree and for the fulfilment of the same they’ve acquired contemplative inspiration that our children are lacking of sacrament due to misuse of modern education and technology. A person who lacks sacrament cannot attain upliftment happily and satisfactorily in any sector. Conserving and protecting the cows in the society

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"br4kjrrot","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"justify","fontWeight":"400","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"p","innerHTML":"

In the year 1987, when there was a severe famine, people were unable to get even potable water. At that time, the condition of cows who have been a motherly figure for us was very piteous. In such an adverse situation, based on the inspiration of Shri Vallabhacharyaji’s principles and Krishna worship, Goswami Shri KishorechandrajiMaharajashri initiated to explain the purest form of Shri Vallabhacharyaji’s principles and established the importance of principles with a noble intuition of creating a joyous and peaceful dwelling for our ‘Gaumata-Gauvansh’ in the entire Saurashtra region and to stop the blot of slaughtering the cows, many sensitive and alert Vaishnavas came forward and ‘Goswami Shri PurushottamlaljiGauseva Trust’ was established. Getting inspired by Goswami Shri KishorechandrajiMaharajashree, it was decided that this trust will undertake the formation and management of ‘Shri VallabhGoshala’.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"up9ot5ocs","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"justify","fontWeight":"400","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{"href":"#"},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"a","innerHTML":"

An appropriate land was chosen near Junagadh at Vadala village where ‘Gaumata-Gauvansh’ can get a natural, beautiful, clean and convenient environment and can be protected against flood and filth.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"trk30pvcw","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"justify","fontWeight":"400","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{"href":"#"},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"a","innerHTML":"

The ‘Bhoomi-Pujan’ ceremony was undertaken in presence of Cheeraayushman Shri Piyushbawashri. On the devout day of ‘NandBawaPraagatya Divas’ MahasudAgiyaras, Gau-pujan was undertaken by Goswami Shri AniruddhLaaljiMaharajashri. Then in the presence of Mahant Shri GopalaNandji (President, Bharat Sadhu Samaj), Gaumata-Gauvansh were welcomed inside the gaushalas for dwelling. Gaumata-Gauvansh have been joyously dwelling here since 2004.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"vowdrp20c","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"justify","fontWeight":"400","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{"href":"#"},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"a","innerHTML":"

Utilizing the advanced technologies and facilities available in the current era as well as maintaining our original culture, the revival of certain obsolete departments was undertaken in 2021.

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"mvj3mkftb","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"justify","fontWeight":"400","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","marginTop":"0px","marginRight":"0px","marginBottom":"16px","marginLeft":"0px","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{"href":"#"},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"a","innerHTML":"

Vision: If we study the importance of Gomata preached omnisciently in Hindu Theology, one thing we can clearly understand that Gomata-Govansh is only the basis of entire creation. With sermon of “गावो विश्वस्य मातरः, मातरः सर्वभूतानां”, our holy scriptures allots Gomata a title of Mother of entire creation and its living beings. It is firmly believed that if a mother is gratified then only she can nurture its offspring excellently. Besides, the basis of happiness and exultation of creation and its living beings are sanctity and holiness & the basis of the same is Gomata. So, if it is thought by this perspective, Go-Aashray or cow conservation is very essential for our steadfast happiness, joy, and growth. Hence comprehending the Go-Aashray or importance of Gomata and the way she is disregarded, let us awaken for Go-Seva&Conservation and awaken the society for this as well!

","customAttributes":{}},{"blockId":"edwejwno3","children":[],"baseStyles":{"fontSize":"16px","height":"fit-content","lineHeight":"1.7","minWidth":"10px","position":"static","top":"auto","left":"auto","textAlign":"justify","fontWeight":"400","color":"#000000","fontFamily":"Quicksand","width":"100%"},"rawStyles":{},"mobileStyles":{"textAlign":"left","width":"100%"},"tabletStyles":{},"attributes":{"href":"#"},"classes":[],"dataKey":null,"element":"a","innerHTML":"

Mission: By abiding above perspective all the time in life, Our Acharya NityaLeela.ShreeKishorchandrajiMaharajshreewho has dedicated his entire life for Go-Seva and with immense inspiration by him the VallabhGoshala has been established that only aims service to cow lineage, conservation and welfare. Considering the holistic wellness of Gomata, the VallabhGoshala has been ready with advanced and enormous facilities under the able guidance of Shree KishorchandrajiMaharajshree.Comprehending the importance of Gomata& putting itintoimplementation, a perception of complete gratification and happiness is only the aim of Shree VallabhGoshala. Simultaneously, Shree VallabhGoshala also cherishes the perception of quality conservation and breeding of cows by our society excellently.

In the year 1987, when there was a severe famine, people were unable to get even potable water. At that time, the condition of cows who have been a motherly figure for us was very piteous. In such an adverse situation, based on the inspiration of Shri Vallabhacharyaji’s principles and Krishna worship, Goswami Shri KishorechandrajiMaharajashri initiated to explain the purest form of Shri Vallabhacharyaji’s principles and established the importance of principles with a noble intuition of creating a joyous and peaceful dwelling for our ‘Gaumata-Gauvansh’ in the entire Saurashtra region and to stop the blot of slaughtering the cows, many sensitive and alert Vaishnavas came forward and ‘Goswami Shri PurushottamlaljiGauseva Trust’ was established. Getting inspired by Goswami Shri KishorechandrajiMaharajashree, it was decided that this trust will undertake the formation and management of ‘Shri VallabhGoshala’.

The ‘Bhoomi-Pujan’ ceremony was undertaken in presence of Cheeraayushman Shri Piyushbawashri. On the devout day of ‘NandBawaPraagatya Divas’ MahasudAgiyaras, Gau-pujan was undertaken by Goswami Shri AniruddhLaaljiMaharajashri. Then in the presence of Mahant Shri GopalaNandji (President, Bharat Sadhu Samaj), Gaumata-Gauvansh were welcomed inside the gaushalas for dwelling. Gaumata-Gauvansh have been joyously dwelling here since 2004.

Vision: If we study the importance of Gomata preached omnisciently in Hindu Theology, one thing we can clearly understand that Gomata-Govansh is only the basis of entire creation. With sermon of “गावो विश्वस्य मातरः, मातरः सर्वभूतानां”, our holy scriptures allots Gomata a title of Mother of entire creation and its living beings. It is firmly believed that if a mother is gratified then only she can nurture its offspring excellently. Besides, the basis of happiness and exultation of creation and its living beings are sanctity and holiness & the basis of the same is Gomata. So, if it is thought by this perspective, Go-Aashray or cow conservation is very essential for our steadfast happiness, joy, and growth. Hence comprehending the Go-Aashray or importance of Gomata and the way she is disregarded, let us awaken for Go-Seva&Conservation and awaken the society for this as well!
